# C++ Naming Conventions

## General Rules
- Use snake_case for all identifiers (functions, variables, file names)
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants and macros
- Use PascalCase for class names and struct names (C++ standard convention)
- Use PascalCase for enum class names (C++ standard convention)

## File Naming
- Header files: `logger.h`, `my_class.h` (snake_case)
- Source files: `logger.cpp`, `my_class.cpp` (snake_case)
- Use lowercase with underscores for all file names

## Function Naming
- All functions: `get_instance()`, `calculate_total()`, `process_data()`
- Private member functions: `get_current_time()`, `level_to_string()`
- Static functions: `create_instance()`, `validate_input()`

## Variable Naming
- Local variables: `user_name`, `total_count`, `is_valid`
- Member variables: `m_name`, `m_count` (optional prefix) or just `name`, `count`
- Parameters: `user_id`, `message_text`, `log_level`
- Constants: `MAX_SIZE`, `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT`

## Class and Struct Naming
- Classes: `Logger`, `DataProcessor`, `NetworkManager` (PascalCase)
- Structs: `UserInfo`, `ConfigData` (PascalCase)

## Enum Naming
- Enum classes: `LogLevel`, `ErrorCode` (PascalCase)
- Enum values: `DEBUG`, `INFO`, `WARNING` (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE)

## Namespace Naming
- Namespaces: `common`, `utils`, `network` (lowercase, snake_case for multi-word)

## Comments
- All comments must be in English
- Use clear, descriptive comments for complex logic
- Document public APIs with clear descriptions

## Code Style
- Use 4 spaces for indentation
- Use braces for all control structures (if, for, while)
- Place opening brace on the same line
- Use const correctness (const methods, const references where appropriate)

